reviews.text: Beautiful building. Well maintained. The stairway up to the museum is awesome. I like the Hawaiian side a lot. The New York side.. not as much. Staff were friendly and polite. Definitely with a quick stop. Is spend about 1 hour tops here. Unless you really like to stop and deeply interpret the art. Do skip the elevator. The stairs are awesome.

I love this museum! It’s free admission and visually captivating. Not only is the building architecture stunning but the art it holds within is also breathtaking. It’s very peaceful. When you go upstairs you have to give your bag to the guard at the desk. Downstairs they have a cafeteria and gift shop. The bathrooms are very nice.
Nice place. A bit small but great pieces to view. The building is beautiful and historic.
I really enjoyed the exibition. It has some wonderful artworks and it is curated very well. Great written descriptions ad to this. The educational room totally amazed me!

This is for the people who love Art for a small fee or even free at the first Friday event of every month. Nicely located, small food place with some work shop. Keep an eye on the Jazz at the front lawn which is happened once a year.
A beautiful church for any occasion, even for a celebration of life funeral. The Pastor there is awesome; even  with limited time, he delivers a powerful, inspirational message.
Brings back alot of Childhood Christian Fellowship memories with Awesome familes and friends! Best place to be raised. Sunday School,  Volleyball, Vocational Bible School.
Really neat church. Also free entry so if you are near by it's worth the stop.

Awesome mahalo for your time and consideration. This is a fine example of architectural design that transcends time. 
Hat's off to the people responsible for the upkeep of this historical and beautiful time capsule. 
Mahalo

We visit Honolulu each year at Christmas to visit family there. One of the highlights of our visit is Christmas service at this sacred church. Wonderful congregation, beautiful and historic structure and one of the most precious Christmas programs that you will ever experience.

Cool place with lots of history about the missionaries and their life in Hawaii. They have a printing press which was great for the kids and adults to see in action.
The old missionary house is the original house from the 1800s.
We had a great tour today led by the curator.  He was very knowledgeable and sincere and you felt he loves what his work and it shows in his presentation.  Thanks.

My wife and I thoroughly enjoyed the guided tour by Docent Rose Hansen 
 through the Mission House buildings on the Kamaaina discount Sat, even though the weather was very rainy. Her attention to detail in sharing the history of the early missionaries in Hawaii, their lifestyle and challenges throughout their time here, their artifacts, and the contributions and influences the missionaries made to our Hawaiian culture and history thru the  printing press, music, fashion, construction, and of course in religion, were most enlightening, and even different from our early understandings. We highly recommend this tour, or even a revisit, to visitors and kamaaina alike.  Mahalo to Curator Mike and Gift Shop assistant Grace for a very memorable experience.

Had a nice tour of the historic buildings.  The history of of the printing press was interesting as was the translation and printing of the bible into the Hawaiian language. 

The gift shop was nice.  Staff were very friendly.
Oh outstanding location for looking at the historical events of our past.. Visit  and judge  for yourself and  share your thoughts...

Located a short walk from Kuakini Hospital, this is a nice little park to have a picnic or stretch your legs.   Although it's in between a bunch of buildings,  it's surprisingly quiet.  We happened to go in the afternoon and the sprinklers were on in one of the areas.  If not, it would also be a really nice place for the kids to run around.

Just be aware that there are only a few parking spaces...but it shouldn't be too much of a problem as people don't linger for a long period of time.  Also, the restrooms are all boarded up so there are no facilities to wash hands or use the restroom.

A small Park that's so serene with the babbling Brook and just good energy. I have also married people there which is really pretty. Some homeless come to visit but seems to be  safe. I go there almost every week and have had a good experience.
Beautiful waterfalls open area and lawns nicely mowed. Needs help with trash pick up and a big minus for family use, the bathrooms are closed up.
The river is polluted, there isn't much to see, and the homeless encampments in the back make it kind of hard to enjoy this spot.  It needs some work for sure.
Although the park has the potential to be beautiful, the amount of trash scattered around deters from everything. Nice waterfall and some ducks

We were on a cruise that parked at pier 11 and were able to easily walk to Iolani Palace. We had signed up on line for a docent lead tour, and it was fantastic. Building is wonderfully renovated. Colleen our tour guide brought the building to life with the history of the royal Hawaiian family. Very enjoyable. very sad to see that the Hawaiian "royalty" imitated European architecture, dress, etc. But it is certainly what they built, and it is well curated and preserved

So much history here, both good and bad. The guided tour is well worth the small extra cost; our tour guide was amazing, happy to answer our questions, extremely knowledgeable, friendly, as were all of the staff and volunteers. 

Our guide was able to strike a good, and no doubt well thought out, balance between telling stories of the good times in the palace and the crimes committed against the Kingdom of Hawaii. 

The palace and grounds are beautiful, the exhibits informative, and the location easy to access via The Bus from anywhere. Bring a picnic lunch or visit Chinatown for great food.

Spectacular !! If you are in Honolulu you MUST visit this place ! 

It has beautiful restoration work. They have self guided audio tour which provides a great insight on Hawaiian history. You cannot touch anything and they provide you with shoe covers,but there are benches inside to sit and listen to the audio.Since you got to return your audio sets after coming out of the palace it gives you a sense that the tour is over,but make sure you don't miss the basement.

The prices of the tickets are worth for what they have to offer ! Do visit this place

We really enjoyed our tour at the Iolani Palace! Our tour guide Phyllis was FANTASTIC! She was so informative and passionate about the history that took place in Hawai'i. We were able to visit many beautiful rooms and take a step back in history. I'm thankful we got to leave better educated about the history of the Aloha state. I'm so happy Phyllis was able to answer all our questions and even tell us more about the area! I definitely recommend stopping by, it's the only official Royal residence in the states!

Go during a major Hawaiian holiday or December, the Palace will be beautifully decorated. You can visit the grounds and watch a documentary for free but you must pay to enter. It is beautiful on the inside and has many historical artifacts. There is an audio tour and docents to answer questions.
A beautiful home. Fit for Hawaiian Royalty

Another great experience at Washington Place. The only issue is the limited parking. The home is kept in very good condition and it is a great venue for military promotions. The governor provided opening remarks and presided in the promotion ceremony.
Great historic place to learn on Hawaiian monarchy history.
Went there to hear Hawaiian music, such a lovely afternoon.
If you ever have the chance to visit you should. This once was the home of our beloved Queen Liliokalani. And the home to Hawaii's first family.
Friendly staff, nice food. We had a banquet for 7 people with a pile of beers. Loads of well prepared, tasty food and reasonably priced as well.
Really nice surroundings lovely friendly staff and great food.  Brilliant value for money.  Well worth a visit.
Fantastic food and friendly service. Only place that has good aromatic crispy duck. They make some great food.
Would give zero stars if possible. Food was terrible, and the service was even worse! Avoid like the plague.
Remember that You have to pay extra money for rice. Beef was... lets say "good" and the service really nice.

Restaurant is quite expensive and for a high price you would expect a certain level of service. My family rarely eats out so we would normally go to this type of establishment only for a special occasion.

Unfortunately during a recent event at 53 By The Sea, my mother had a negative experience due to the behavior of one of the staff. Apparently a banquet server named "Jeff" was both rude and dismissive during service. He was not attentive and did not respond at all to inquiries.

Part of going to a nice restaurant involves the food. Part involves the ambiance. But a big part of the experience is based on how customers are treated by staff. Due to Jeff and his interactions we had a negative experience and are not likely to eat at this restaurant again.

Loved everything about it. I got the scallops and my fiancee got the tomahawk steak! He says it was the best steak he has ever had. I am not a huge steak eater but it was Delicious and Juicy. Lobster rolls were amazing! Great views and a truly wonderful evening.

This is another of Hawaii's ultimate dining destinations. The restaurant itself is very impressive (the staircase on arrival is unlike anything i have seen in a restaurant before) and the outlook back to the city very pretty. 
The food was brilliant, though it was disappointing that the wine list was missing 3 of the wines we first chose and the menu was missing 3 key dishes(To be fair it was new year's day). 

Otherwise, a very good restaurant.

Excellent service. We were there for lunch on Valentine’s Day after having a beach wedding. Food was delicious and presented beautifully.  All the staff that we encountered were so helpful and added to the enjoyable experience
Hubby brought me here for a night out and it was great!! The atmosphere is warm, delightful, and very romantic!! Great place for date night!! We will definitely be coming back!!

A nice little place in China Town. I was a little dubious at first, (waitress didn't make us feel welcome) but food was sooo good! Good quality and great flavors! No alcohol, but you can bring your own I guess? Very inexpensive ($10-12) for main dish. I would go back.

Everybody's favorite restaurant in Chinatown! The Chan's have been in business in Honolulu for decades satisfying local and visitor alike. Little village is the jewel in their crown. Always excellent oh, always bustling. Worth the wait if there is one. And the street outside is the floor show. Chinatown is the most interesting historic neighborhood in Honolulu
Loved it. Spring rolls, hot and sour soup, beef broccoli noodles, Mongolian beef, and orange chicken. Delicious! Dessert was tasty and simple, almond float and mango pudding. Be back soon!!!

Have lived this restaurant for many years.  Located in Honolulu's Chinatown, it is always busy, a testament to the great tasting food.  My favorite?  Honey Walnut Chicken.  Park in any if the nearby public lots.  It walk from.nearby offices.  Also convenient to many bus routes.
This is an awesome place. Best Chinese food in Chinatown. Always great food, and great service. Super clean family owned. Rib eye steak stir fried fantastic

the best way I can describe it is great awesome Chinese food that will exceed expectation.. the dim sum absolutely exceptional. as well as any dish you ordered. each step over there pays absolute attention to every detail of your Exceptional dining experience.
Always satisfied with Mandalay food and service.  Linda is always so accommodating.  Celebrated my son's 25th birthday and my Good friends Michael and Joseph's latest visit to Hawaii.

So many of my friends have commented on  how great Mandalay's Buffets are when it's offered. Well, I finally ate their tonight, Christmas Day, with my family.  It is all they said. The food, lots of delicious Chinese dishes and Prime Rib done perfectly. The quality and attention to details is A+++. And a bonus, they offer a Seniors price.

Mandalay is one of the best Chinese restaurants I have ever eaten at! The food is absolutely fantastic. I highly recommend any kind of seafood from Mandalay, you will not be disappointed! The venue is nice. The restaurant has a relaxing but still social feeling. This is a great restaurant for getting together with friends and family.
Delicious cuisine, served in a unique style. Service was excellent and the atmosphere was welcoming

Enjoyed our first visit to Zippy's! I've looked forward to having it since we don't have any back in Texas. The food was delicious and there were many things to choose from! I got the Korean Fried Chicken with white rice and my other family member got friend Chicken with white rice and Macaroni Salad. I look forward to visiting again! Thank you Zippy's for making our trip memorable!

Almost always a good experience here. Although they often have trouble with homeless folks hanging around, today was good. They put up locks on the bathrooms so that has helped deter them from coming in.  Wait staff are friendly, even if not quick, and seemingly patient with 3 kids making a ton of noise and tossing food around. Food was served quickly after ordering, cooked nicely (omelettes, French toast and pancakes). Bacon and hash browns could have been more "crispy", but still tasty.
Great food and service. It was recommended by a local and no disappointment. Bakery is full of Hawaiian goodies. Definitely would eat here again.

Didn't have to wait ,walked in at the right time on Sunday morning.
Food was wonderful,portion was just right.Server was cheerful and
Helped me with suggestions for
My entire.Food was good my younger brother cleaned his plate,
I took some home.
Meeting room is large, clean, and comfortable for your club or group gathering. Employees are super friendly with a positive attitude. Food quality is above average.

Best place to go hiking with family or friends. If you are up for hiking, be ready with your outfit. Wear your most comfortable hiking gears. Rubber shoes and gym clothes are recommended. Bring plenty of water and keep hydrated. There is only one toilet on the parking area, so make sure use the most out of it.

Perfect hike for all ages below 65.  Took our fit family about 50 min round trip and that includes spending 10 min enjoying the view from the top. Bring water and celebrate when done by splurging at the Dole food truck in the parking lot.

Really fun hike, not too difficult nor is it too easy. Plenty of great views along the way as well. You also get to go inside and on top of old World War II bunkers. Very fun and interesting, if you're visiting Hawaii or you just like hiking, this is definitely the place to go.

This is a short, but challenging hike.  When you get to the top you get to walk through some old WWII pillboxes. This is a very popular place.  Parking can be an issue. We took the city bus and walked into the park.  The view from the summit is worth the effort. Take your time. Wear good shoes. Bring water. Most of all, be prepared to climb.

The best hike ever and it will take an average person about 30-40 minutes to get to the tip top and it's worth it. Bring full bottle of water & good pair of tennis shoes. Trails are uneven in some places and there's a tunnel so if you are claustrophobic & it will get a bit dark inside as you walk thru the low ceiling tunnel.. just a note of caution.. There are stairs as well , one set which is very long and steep, but there's an alternate route which is a little longer but easier route. The stairs will be a challenge for some.  I think there were 3 sets of stairs. None of the photos here are pics of the tip top 😁 but I made it. I recommend hiking in the morning. It was 4:00 when I started and I think it was way too hot. Also the latest you can start hiking is 4:30. There's a juice truck near the parking lot and at 6:00 it is closed. Buy your pineapples and juice before 6:00

Super fun but not to be under estimated as I had to help 2 people that had fainted. Only hike this if you are fit and have good shoes, are well hydrated. Bring water and food. Views from top are well worth it. No charge to park or hike. Know your limits, my wife stopped about 1/2 way up, nothing wrong with that.

Man the top, BEAUTIFUL! The hike though is not a laughing matter, it is very physical demanding at least for myself since am average physically fit. Was able to finished but with lots of 1 minute breaks in between  and at points felt I wasn't going to be able to finish of how exhausting it was and long. But if you're game, take your own time don't push yourself too hard or others in your group, take plenty of water for the hike up and for when you get back down, as well as sunblock. Enjoy the top, the middle or even just a little above the bottom, each have their own nice views to enjoy.

Rustic garden in the crater. Easy walk around, can probably be a little steamy if it's hot. Bring bug dope. Also be prepared to see some pretty amazing trees and foliage. We have visited botanical gardens around the world and still saw some new trees. No charge, no amenities, no dogs but easy to find and a well spent couple of hours.

This was such an adventure! Wasn't sure if it would be worth it once we started the trek up, but it was definitely worth it! I would recommend this to anyone who is physically able to do it. Its exhausting, but you'll always be thankful you did it. Advise, go before 8am, bring water, maybe some light snacks for the top, a camera, and someone with you. The "stairs" were rough climbing up and coming down, but the way down is much easier. The view at the top is like no other. If you're in the area this is something you should definitely do! I would do this again, and again.

Awesome botanical garden with interesting terrain and a plethora of amazing plants to look at.  It is a desert environment within the crater and it is surprising how many beautiful plants are able to thrive in such dry conditions.  If you have some time and like a little hike come and visit this gem.

We highly recommend this for families with younger children. Our kids loved the touch tanks where they could feed fish and the aviary with colorful birds that landed on them. The trained dolphins were an absolute delight to watch. Our visit here was very memorable.

Park is good. Several exhibits were closed for renovations. Shows and learning opportunities were great.

 Luau was amazing; great food, great performers.
Down time in-between park closing until going into luau area was long and challenging.

Did the Luau here and had a great time.  They had a decent menu and excellent entertainment. With the Luau you get passes to the park which we didn't have the time to check it out.  But just based on the entrance with all the turtles I knew it would be a place we go to on our next visit to Hawaii.  Kids really enjoyed it.

If you have been to other Sea Life's across the world this one may be a bit small. However coming from the middle of Canada we found it amazing. The dolphin experience was wonderful and to our surprise our favourite spot was the bird enclosure. They give you a stick filled with bird feed and you can feed any number of the 500 birds in the enclosure. Be prepared for them to land all over you. Absolutely wonderful experience! 

We will be back!

My family and I had a great time. Initial impression wasn't great. The guide that accompanied the bus driver had an attitude and was snippy-that really rubbed me the wrong way-because we were unsure of the exact location of the bus terminal. 
When we arrived at the park, we found all the employees very nice and helpful. They were more than happy to answer questions and they ensured you understood exactly what to do.
Excellent food and service. Great location on the ocean with great views. Friendly staff...

My boyfriend and I treated ourselves to a nice dinner here on our last night before heading back to the mainland. Beyond the elegance, food, and view, what (or rather who) really made this such a great experience was one of our servers, Tony. He was SO human and nice with us that we found we were keeping him at our table just to keep the conversation going! We really wanted to let everyone and Hoku's know how much we appreciated his service. If you're in need of some excellent food and a bright shining face, just ask for Tony over your meal at Roku's! Thank you Tony!
Excellent service and food!! My husband and I had a great time for our wedding anniversary dinner!!!
Absolutely amazing dining experience, on par with a Michelin Star establishment. The most cordial & professional service I have ever personally had.

I never knew this place was open for breakfast, but during the holiday season it has a great buffet that opens at 730 am.  very attentive staff, and a great view too. George took care of us, he is a very kind man, I enjoyed our chat. Mahalo, see you again soon.

Japanese take-out restaurant.  Small menu (5-7 menu options) that varies day to day.  Only open for lunch.  Outside seats only, somewhat shaded.  Menu prices are from around $6-11.  Good portion size, pretty good lunch, food was quick.

Das Irifune ist ein traditionelles Restaurant seit 1974. Die neue Location ist ganz nett, nichtmehr so eng wie früher.
Der garlic ahi ist mit der beste den es auf der Insel gibt.
Die Bento schmeckt gut, leider fehlen ein paar Gerichte zu früher.
Wäre schön wenn ihr in Zukunft auch Abend geöffnet hättet.
Schön das es euch wieder gibt.

reviews.author_name: たまくろうチャンネル

reviews.text: Great food, though a bit pricy, but we're looking for a taste of local food and this place doesn't disappoint.  I was here 3 years ago and it was good back then, and it was just as good today.  Pork is cooked long and slow and it just melted in our mouth.  Coming from San Fran, our $115 for lunch for 6 was not bad.  Highly recommend the combos and make sure to get extra bowls of rice!  Kimchi is also really good!!

Definitely would recommend the kalua pig and laulau. This is a no frills place, so don't expect a true restaurant. I would give a full 5 starts if the price was more reasonable. The dishes are very small and pretty expensive for what you get.

But again, delicious and would recommend if you want some true Hawaiian fare.
Authentic spot, nice old school style. Not many places left like this. Enjoy it while you still can!

Great past reviews so was looking forward to this meal but must have had an off day when I was there. Nothing on my plate had a great taste and staff made me feel like I was not worth the effort of good service.
Most of my Hawaiian vocabulary comes from this dinner. Chicken long rice, short ribs and Kalua pork were personal highlights. Taste local, Chinese and Korean out of them.

We went for a school field trip with 3rd graders. The students were able to draw in their journals in and around the museum.  The docents were knowledgeable and kept the children's interest the whole time. Beautiful and peaceful garden home with intriguing artwork indoors and out.

One of my favorite places in the entire state! Gorgeous setting, outstanding art -- check out the Hockney exhibit! -- a fantastic indoor/outdoor café, and a not-to-be-missed gift shop.  Take a tour of the magnificent grounds when you're done with the museum!

Great art museum!  Their galleries are quite  fascinating. The different mediums throughout the museum is terrific.  
 The local art is amazing and the different galleries that they change out every few months are very interesting and unique.  The 3rd Sunday of each month is Family Day with arts and crafts for the kids,family films and usually live music and dancing. Its a super fun event!

This small but mighty museum is one of the most charming places on Oahu. You get well curated exhibits at a spectacular property. You could take a quick break up here and feel instantly transported or languish here for hours for a mindful retreat. 

I recommend checking it out first on the Bank of Hawaii Family Sunday’s (the 3rd Sunday each Month) when admission to this museum and its sister, the Honolulu Museum of Art on S. Beretania are completely free. While it’s typically crowded on those days; you can at least get a sense of the space. If you enjoy it, then come back another day and take advantage of the tours. The volunteer docents are extremely friendly and approachable. They know how to coax great conversations out of you even if you feel like you don’t know anything about art. 

One of my absolute favorite places in the world!!

I love it at the Spalding house cafe. What can be any better then looking out at the city on a nice beautiful sunny day, with a wonderful picnic basket prepared by the wonderful people in the cafe. Celebrating how lucky we live Hawaii with a bottle a wine that I brought to relax and enjoy with friends. With the picnic basket had the Classic panini and the Chicken Reuben Sandwiches. It also came with salad, dessert, and drinks. They also provided us with a blanket, umbrella, and chirping bird of paradise...I would recommend this experience to anyone who has never seen the city through in this kind of sunlight.❤💙💚💛🧡💜

I have lived I Hawaii for over 40 years and this is the first time I have stepped foot at this amazing historical location. I regret not going before because I feel I really missed out.  I almost dare to say that it is better then the Iolani Palace.  There is a guided walking tour that really is full of amazing historical information and paints a complete picture of those that lived there and things that led up to their possessions and related historical facts that you just can't get out of a history book. 

You don't need much time there, but I would allow a total of 1.5 hours to fully enjoy.  There is so much to see and study inside the house and the surrounding property is very beautiful with all the tropical landscaping.

It is very inexpensive to visit and they do offer different discounts, but it is so inexpensive, it is almost unnecessary.  

Location is easy to get to, but parking might be a challenge depending on time and day of the week. There is a park just behind that has parking spaces and you can walk across the field to the site. It is a rainy area, so an umbrella might be a good idea just in case.

What a great part of Hawaii's history. If you are staying in Waikiki or Honolulu in general I highly recommend this. The docent was very informative and tour was detailed. I enjoyed it very much! Best part was that you may take pictures! Always a plus in historic houses!

IT'S LONG! Docents here do NOT have Aloha spirit. When we arrived there were 3 of them chatting together right in the entrance. We saw a sign that we had to remove our shoes. My husband walks with a cane but there was a bench so he sat to remove his shoes. Then we stood to go in and they said we had to go around to the Gift Shop first. Sat and put shoes back on. Volunteer in Gift Shop had Aloha spirit and explained that the tour was $8 for seniors. Back to entrance again, removed shoes and joined 2:00 tour in progress. She was very knowledgeable and we enjoyed the tour. On leaving I asked the woman at the door if she would return the laminated sheets to the office. "We ask you to do that. " I  told her I wasn't feeling well and handed them to her. I put on my shoes and turned to go. She stepped right in my path to talk to someone else and wouldn't move. I stepped around her.
Not sure if these ladies were being deliberately rude or just stupid. Also, while my husband was waiting for me to get the tickets he overheard one women advising the others to not engage the visitors or ask any questions as their jobs were to get people out as quickly as possible 🤨. 
It still was interesting and I  enjoyed the history!
Historic place of royalty. Suggest touring and then relaxing in the park behind. There's a huge mango tree that makes for a yummy treat in the tree's shade.

Amazing. Going there and be able to walk around and see the things that Queen Emma use while she lived in that Palace was breathtaking seeing the history and the life was amazing price was a little too much for only getting five or six rooms worth Ewing but if you wait for the tour guide to walk you through it makes it worth it.

If only our streets were as well maintained as the trails. I go every week to restore my soul...to hear birds and 
crickets instead of street noise, to smell clean air, earth and flowers to get away from pounding concrete and run free through mud and rocks and roots and ESPECIALLY to enjoy spectacular views of my beloved Hawaii. I hate going in the ocean (yuck!), but I enjoy the beauty of it when I am way up there and it is way down and out there!

Good hiking trails, it's a little muddy in places but the views are very nice.  The bamboo forest is cool especially if a wind is blowing making the clacking sound.  And as a bonus we had the trail to ourselves. Monoa falls trail was full of people.

There is always enough parking although we dont need it because we walk or run to get there. The trail is always great for site seeing rain or shine and is willing to reveal her bountiful secrets. The trail is interconnected with many other diverse trails so potentially your hike could reach seventh heaven.  The key is being quiet, alert, listening, open minded, somewhat fearless, use good common sense, observant.
Quite, cool Manoa breeze, easy trail.
Somewhat muddy but very light traffic.

Beautiful view from this place. Very few tourists actually come here, and this place is usually not crowded, you will see 2-3 people hardly. But go there with your own car as the phone reception is very low so it will be difficult to book an Uber from here.

I love the view here! It is absolutely gorgeous. There are also small picnic areas nearby. I would just like to mention that the parking lots are very small. The road to get there is also very windy. There are no Street lights and people may speed on that road as well. I advise caution when coming to this view. Overall, the view is stunning and definitely worth a visit.

Amazing view of Honolulu, Waikiki beach and the Diamond Head Crater! We especially enjoyed the drive on the small winding road on the way to the top. The parking lot is small, we've got lucky to find a parking spot there, get ready that you may need to wait, but people don't stay for long and it's breathtaking.

Very nice lookout over Honolulu, Diamond Head, and Waikiki. Would highly recommend. Not much parking at the lookout but more parking at the picnic area/bathrooms. Narrow winding road to navigate to the top.

Amazing place to see diamond head and the Honolulu, Waikiki skyline.
Sunsets are also pretty spectacular and the skyline after dark will take your breath away.
Parking can get tight but there are two parking lots and the walk down from the first lot isn't bad.

Possibly the best spring rolls I've ever had. The fried rice was also excellent. They were able to accommodate our large group of adults and children. It wasn't too busy and the staff was friendly and responsive. I knocked off a star because the Pad Thai was just mediocre and multiple people in our party that ordered the summer role really didn't like it due to the mint. So just find and stick to the menu items that you like....like the insanely delicious spring rolls.
This Bangkok Chef in Manoa is so delicious... Monday thru Friday. I think the chef is different on the weekends :(
From the service and food is all great.
Good food. Fast service.
Little hidden gem with great food!

Possibly the best spring rolls I've ever had. The fried rice was also excellent. They were able to accommodate our large group of adults and children. It wasn't too busy and the staff was friendly and responsive. I knocked off a star because the Pad Thai was just mediocre and multiple people in our party that ordered the summer role really didn't like it due to the mint. So just find and stick to the menu items that you like....like the insanely delicious spring rolls.
This Bangkok Chef in Manoa is so delicious... Monday thru Friday. I think the chef is different on the weekends :(
From the service and food is all great.
Good food. Fast service.
Little hidden gem with great food!
Always good, only place I've ever had green thai iced tea, which tastes amazing and looks beautiful! Fresh mango with sticky rice is exceptional. Owners are kind,  great service!
One of our favorite restaurants and has been for over 15yrs!!! Great people and fast service!! Worth every penny!

I ordered crab Rangoon's and pad see ewe.  The wontons were horrible, barely filled with crab or cream cheese they were filled with a dime size it was ridiculous.  The pad see ewe had so much chicken and barely any noodles, the flavor was bland.  Thai is my favorite and I had never eaten here before, and never will.  There are better thai spots out there. Do no order from here.
Food is so yummy and what makes it even better is how incredibly nice the owner is to our kids and family! We feel so very welcome every time!

Ordered delivery. Soup and food tasted like they used too much fish sauce. Curry did not taste like curry and was watery with no coconut milk. No rice included with meal. Chicken looked like low quality scraps and tasted chewy and overcooked. Paid way too much and threw at least 2/3 away. Will never eat food from here again.

staff are super pleasant and helpful.  Oden is most known item on menu.  Rice is from Hokkaido.   rice is cooked Old School.  its a more delicate process but tastes better than electric cooker.  highly recommend!
The customer service,clean,and interior is just comfort style. The best is so ONO!!! ( Excellent ) & real home cooking
I love this place the food is authentic Japanese, the atmosphere is also the same.  They always have a special for the night, the duck is a must if they are serving.  One of the Best NABE in town.

reviews.author_name: ハワイ食べ歩き-ハワイグルメガイド
reviews.text:
こちらのお店は、岡山県　湯原温泉　八景のハワイ支店です。
ランチもあり。懐石料理から、一品料理、そして、デザートまであり。
とてもおいしくいです。
ゆっくり上品な日本料理を食べたい時にお勧めです。
ハワイ在住のアメリカ人のお勧めのお店です。ホノルルへ来て5ヶ月ぶりの懐石料理を堪能しました。いいお店です。

A great hole in the wall Japanese restaurant specializing in udon dishes. Service is quick and friendly. Food options range between Japanese curry to tempura to their well known udon dishes. There's a parking lot along King Street and a parking lot in the back, accessible from Young Street. It can get busy during lunch and dinner time, but there is a sign in sheet on the door and benches in front to wait on. Service is fairly fast so the wait time usually isn't too long.
Fairly decent Japanese Udon I would say for American standards. Tempura was good but thought the batter was a little on the heavier side. But overall good dinner.
One of my favorite places to eat, I always go here at least twice every time I visit Hawaii.

I spent a year in Japan and this restaurant smelled and felt just like the little noodle shops I passed on my way home from a long day of work. Comfort food to be sure. I had the nabeyaki udon just like in those huge steaming kettles sold by street vendors outside the train station. they make their noodles by hand. I also had the fried mochi, served in a soy ginger sauce with sliced green onion.

The outside looks a bit rundown, but the inside is quite nice. The servers were not bothersome and moved quickly to serve everyone. Also, it is a bit cramped inside. As for the food, it was different. The soup base was not salty for once, and the blend of ingredients made it "clean" tasting. Their prices seems a little high, but most of their ingredients are imported from Japan, adding more authenticity to their dishes.

Awesome small place.  There is a line that moves quickly.  CASH ONLY, so be prepared 5 dollars per shave ice.  It was delicious.  They offer condensed milk on top and that took it to the next level.  Definitely recommend adding the condensed milk to any flavors.

Great little mom-and-pop store, with Shave Ice. They have a very very fine iced shave ice, and it's really good. Make sure you ask for extra syrup so that it goes all the way through your ice! This is one of the best places to go when you're down on Waikiki and don't want to go to the tourist traps. I might be a little bit of a line, but well worth it. Definitely recommended!

I got the strawberry and pog flavored shave ice over vanilla ice cream. The ice was smooth and tasted especially good with the creamy ice cream at the bottom. There was always a line here, but they churn these things out quick so the wait is very minimal.

There are some benches along the side of the shop which was nice to sit and eat and people watch. Great place!

Waiola is by far the best shave ice in Oahu. The syrups flavorings are awesome and the texture of the shave ice is flat ahead of any other shave ice place on the island. Prices are reasonable. The locals are regulars.
Best shaved ice... period!  The texture is snow-like! The Hawaii 5-0 Rainbow ice cream bowl with sweetened milk on top is my favorite! 😋

Need to have an local address with proof or they will charge you the tourist price of 19 dollars per so be prepared. Nice for kids, very safe for them to run around. Family friendly, great parking. You pay in the parking lot at little kiosks and they text you if the time will expire and you can pay for more on your phone, it's pretty convenient!!!!! Excellent experience, nice aloha spirited staff!!!!! Hoping to go again pretty soon!!!!!!

It's a nice zoo. Gave us something to do in Hawaii with kids, besides swimming,  tanning, etc.
It is located on a good chunk of land, so there is quite some walking to do.
Nice playground for kids, animals were all out and we were able to see each one of them. 
They do have cool birds,  turtles, reptiles.
Nice landscape and good upkeep.
They have a cute giraffe made for kids to play around & take pics of, I wish they had a few more of animals similar to that.

The zoo is a very large property with lots of green space and a great place to get away from relax from the busy streets. All of the animals had plenty of roaming space which is always something I appreciate seeing at zoos. There were quite a few exhibits that were closed on our visit but other than that we enjoyed seeing and learning about the animals.

The zoo was pleasant and relatively clean but some areas were abandoned and still under construction I think it's a work-in-progress I think it's important to let the public know what's going on and why. The zoo itself was okay I would give it better review if things were a little more cleaned up just an easy to see me. Thank you

Somewhat smaller than other well known zoos, but quite expansion in its own right and well laid out. In February the temperature was about 72 to 75 so wasn't too hot or cool. Large banyan tree is focus point near children's play area, but can be seen from many locations. Out nicest experiences there were meeting (2) local young American military couples there for the day. Extremely pleasant way to spend 2 or 3 quieter, relaxing hours. This was our third visit to Honolulu, so we decided to tour the zoo, and were glad we did.

This beach is beautiful. Every one must visit this place. You will love it. It’s inexpensive to get to while your visiting the island. Bring food and please respect the area, it’s really a great atmosphere

Great place to take kids. The water is shallow enough so the kids can play in the water and it doesn't get deep to fast. It's a man made lagoon so there is no surf s it's not connected to the ocean. Great place to learn to paddle boarding as there are no waves so the water is smooth. You can catch many sizes of fish but you have to do it by hand, they don't allow fishing poles there. Lots of rental equipment to choose from for ocean activities as this is Waikiki.

At the very far west of Waikiki is Kahanamoku Beach. It's a tourist favorite.  There is not much snorkling but the is ocean life by the reef wall that protects the beach from any waves.  Very calm and safe area.
Couple of homeless people on beach area..   but super nice, had a conversation with them...  no worries!!!

Lol don't come here when the wind is high - the sand will slap your body so hard. 

Otherwise, if you're looking for some challenge and have water shoes (it's very rocky), the waves here are strong and warm. 🌊

Wow, one of the best breakfasts we had. The eggs Benedict was outstanding. The steak and eggs was excellent. Such an amazing place to eat breakfast or any meal. It is right down by the beach what hbthe waves roll in and surfers ride the waves. Just awesome.

This place was so nice! The seating was right on the beach, the food was beautiful, quick, fresh and tasty! The line moved fairly quickly and the workers were extremely friendly and funny. It was a great place for our Sunday brunch! Pictured is the pineapple smoothie and the meat and eggs with Portuguese sausage.

What a lovely location, and beautiful view!  Happened across a local ukelele jam session while I was there, such a neat treat!  You can dine in the shade or out on the patio overlooking the ocean. The food here was spectacular, both in presentation and in freshness. I highly recommend the fresh fish and the fresh pineapple smoothie, you won't be disappointed!  Looking forward to visiting again on my next trip!

This is an adorable little cafe with great food and the perfect atmosphere for a bite to eat by the water. Walk up and order what you would like, self seating, and they call your name when your food is ready.  The pineapple smoothie is a must! The bread pudding is delicious and their create your own omelets are fresh and tasty!

Barefoot Beach Cafe lives up to all the rave reviews. We had 4 different meals in our group and all were excellent (especially my Eggs Benedict on Kahlua pork). There was not a long line and the food came out quickly. The location was fantastic for beautiful views/photo ops and fish feeding after. Highly recommend!

Not sure if this is the original location. No frills counter to order your food and limited seating inside and six tables outside. Hum, what to order - a single,  sounds just right; a double, will the bun hold it; or the triple, outrageously huge. Do you even need fries? You don’t say onion rings... I’m full already. Recommend ordering a single with fries. You will not be disappointed. Aloha!

We only ate here one time while we were in town. It was the day we got in town and we had been on a plane all day. I don’t know if it was just that good or we were just that hungry but it was delicious. The service was good and the food was fresh. If you are looking for a good burger I don’t think you could find a better one on the island.

Good burgers, great fries, decent meal, but a bit on the pricier end. My chief motivation for eating at Teddy's was due to Chase Pay running a $5 discount offer. While I don't regret choosing to eat there, I certainly would not have gone out of my way to eat at Teddy's without the offer.

The double burger was hefty - so much so that I had some initial concern that I might not be able to eat it all (that proved unfounded). The fries were however the real star of the meal - deliciously crispy, just how I like them.

The decor and atmosphere of the place is a throwback, and they share a coded bathroom with the hotel next door.

Awesome place for Vegitarian and meat burgers.  The staff was super friendly and helped everybody works through the three menus. One of them in Korean, one of them in Japanese, and one in English. They took the time to help my family work through our order.  We had veggie burgers with the spicy sauce and it was amazing! I would definitely recommend this place to anybody who's looking for great service and great food.
Teddy's is the best burger on the beach, maybe beyond. Skip a meal or two and get a double. Fun decor, great staff, and good food.

Good, fresh and quality food.  the location is easy, no problem with the parking lot. Reasonable prices, delicious food cooked to perfection. I'm not a fan of noodles, but this one making me feel to come for more. Friend people, approachable staff, good service with the effort to feel the customer more comfortable and relax. I highly recommend these places for awesome experiences.

Can’t post a photo, my bowl is empty! Amazing prices in a pricey resort town. Delicious, for sure check the slow times, super fast service! At lunch rush the line was down the street. That’s what drew my attention to try it out. So happy I did!

There will be a long line of people but not a long wait for your food once you order. They are quick so pay attention and be ready to order when they ask. Everything on the menu can be ordered by number to simplify things even more. Food was good and so were the prices. You can spend very little or spend a bit more and indulge but still won't go broke.

Be prepared to wait if you come after 5pm. Can be decently priced if you just get noodles. Everything on the menu is good. The specials is a must try. Once it's gone they don't come back for awhile, and it's always changing. Seating can be difficult when busy. If your a party of two don't hog the big booths, they will move you to maximize space. Everything else is straightforward. Order by number to keep things simple, move forward get your side goodies then pay. They also do take out. Not to sure if they do phone orders. On hot days I like to order the cold version of whatever.

I can honestly say this is the best Udon I've ever had! Freshly made noodles that are just the right texture and bite. The broth was very flavorful, especially when you mix it in with the egg. There is also a tempura buffet of shrimp, sweet potato and much more to pair it with. 

We were lucky enough to get there with no line, around 3pm on a weekday. But the long line is worth it for this delicious udon!

While in town for a few weeks, I ate here almost every day. That is not an exaggeration. Almost every day. The food is delicious, the service is fantastic, and (by Waikiki standards) the price is extremely reasonable. A five star rating does not do the business justice. Throughout that time, I was not able to find a single bad thing on the menu (though the Pineapple Pork Chop is far and away my favorite dish). Down to the coffee, there is not a single thing which you will find disappointing. 

Though, I do feel the need to warn anyone reading this: there will be a line. If you are not there right when they open, there will be a line almost stretching into the street. You may find yourself waiting 45 minutes or longer for food. So be cautious of that, or get there extremely early. But, if you find you do get there early enough or are willing to wait, you will find amazing food to start your day off with.

Long wait, but well worth it. Get there early to avoid the long line. The food was delicious and satisfying. The buttermilk pancakes are a must have! You pay upfront after ordering which is awesome because you can just get up and leave once you are done eating. They accept credit cards. The only downside is the occasional birds in the restaurant.

The pancakes here are out of this world! I don't normally order pancakes because they're just typically not prepared and executed correctly. I ordered these pancakes four separate times in different forms and each time they exceeded expectations. They're literally the perfect pancake. You won't find a better one anywhere else! You MUST have some!

Amazing fresh local food! I now have been to the one in Guam and Hawaii both amazing. Thanks for the fast and heart customer service. Recommend to everyone. Plan for a wait in line, this is very popular place.

Rich in the beach theme, and amazing hospitality! Loved the environment. If you are looking for fancy, this is not the spot. But if you're looking for the Hawaiian experience, this place if perfect!
The best waffles in the area. Did I mention the great hospitality?!

Place is really popular amongst Korean tourists, and the ARMY fandom of BTS. Seating is generally very quick, food options are amazing. A bit pricey but that's to be expected since that's how it is in Waikiki. Though to be fair the sizing of each dish is very big, so you're getting your money's worth. I went alone and that's usually fine but I recommend going with another person or more since the food fills you up. I also love the little drawings and written notes they laminate and post all over the walls, makes it feel more homey. You can also cook food on the built in table grill. I do suggest asking which items they have that's for grilling though since it doesn't clearly say on any of the menus

American in Mom and pop style Korean restaurant on a side street with seating for maybe 40 people. Most meals about $30 my entrée was $20 (spicy chicken with vegetables ). Brought a half dozen side dishes before bringing a main dish. Which was very large. These were delicious including kimchi. Some sides spicy some not. Wife and I had several glasses of wine, six dollars per glass with extremely large pours,maybe 10 ozs. Our server spoke clear and fluent English. Menu in both Korean and English. Wife who has lived in Asia for a few years said food was authentic.
Quality of Korean dishes need to get better. Just horribly cooked dishes. The owner is only interested in making more profits out of tourists.

I love Korean food. We’ve been to this place twice. First time when we just arrived at Honolulu and were really tired and jet lagged. So we decided not to judge too stern. But the second time we had similar experience. So... Food was OK. Not sure that they brought what my husband ordered. But it was ok, we were tired, not a big deal. He ordered hot soup, they brought hot soup. Different kind, but soup. Never mind. Who cares. Both times, wait was toooo long. We almost fell asleep over there. Then we found out that other people who came after us got their food already. Then I got my food. Then my husband got his. Ten minutes later. What do I do? Eat while it’s hot or wait ten more minutes so we could eat together? Choices, choices...
Not a big fan of that kind of service.
The best Korean food in Waikiki. Been eating here for over 10 years and satisfied with every dish I try.

Brilliant, I think that’s the only word I can use. Service was some of the best I’ve had, ever. Incredibly attentive staff who took orders, knew the menus perfectly and took the work in their stride. 
The food was presented delicately and precisely with loads of flavour. Seafood was cooked to precision on both the scallops and the prawns. Meat flavours were juicy and soft and overall a really spectacular evening had by everyone. Highly recommend for birthdays and intimate evenings with a loved one, spectacular views and spectacular service

We spent our last evening in Oahu at the Top of Waikiki and it was the best decision. There was a happy hour special which was amazing- the food was delicious. The drinks were so yummy but what made it so fabulous was the bartenders- James, Reggie, and Sean. They’re the best and were so much fun! They made our night.  John the manager was also great and super nice. Next time we come back to Oahu we’ll definitely stop here and hopefully James, Reggie, and Sean will be there!
Our second time and it was as wondeful as the first! Our waiter Chris was excellent! The view is great and cool to see the kids' reaction to rotating around. I highly recommend!!
Great views while dining. Revolving Restaurant overlooking Waikiki Beach and Mountain Views. Food is good. Service is spot on. Is pricey however.

It would be nice if they stuck to the dress code here. It is supposed to be a NICE restaurant and they let people wearing t-shirts and baseball caps be seated for dinner.  The food was good after waiting an hour to be served.  We opted for no desserts and only one drink because again we waited an hour for our dinner and were not asked if we wanted another within that time.
